def barplot_platforms(df, plist):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=len(plist) // 3 + len(plist) % 3, ncols=3, figsize=(16, 16))
    axes = axes.flatten()

    for i in range(len(plist)):
        g = plist[i]
        df.loc[(g, )].plot.bar(
            width=0.9, ax=axes[i],
            xlabel=ru_name['year_of_release'],
            ylabel=' ',
            title=f'     {g} \n '
        );

    plt.subplots_adjust(left=0, bottom=0, right=1, top=1, wspace=0.15, hspace=0.5)

def plot_scatter_actual(plf):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=2, figsize=(14, 4))
    for i, n in enumerate(['critic_score', 'user_score']):
        games_actual[(games_actual[n] != -1) & (games_actual['platform'] == plf)].plot.scatter(
            x=n, y='total_sales', alpha=0.5, ax=axes[i],
            title=f'    {plf}',
            xlabel=ru_name[n],
            ylabel=ru_name['total_sales']
        )

In[173]:
regions = {'na_sales':'North America', 'eu_sales':'Europe', 'jp_sales':'Japan'}
pars = ['rlsd', 'sold (mln)', 'sold/rlsd', 'sold %'] # released (rlsd)

#      
def group_by_reg(cat, region):
    gbr_df = (games_actual.groupby(cat)[region]
            .agg(['count', 'sum', 'mean'])
            .sort_values(by='sum', ascending=False)
            .reset_index())
    gbr_df['%'] = gbr_df['sum'] * 100 / gbr_df['sum'].sum()
    if gbr_df.shape[0] > 5:
        nr = gbr_df.loc[5:, :].sum()
        gbr_df = gbr_df[:5].copy()
        nr[cat] = 'Other'
        gbr_df.loc[5] = nr
    gbr_df.columns = [cat]+pars
    return gbr_df

#       
def regional_top(cat, draw_pies=True):
    full_table = pd.concat([group_by_reg(cat, 'na_sales'),
                            group_by_reg(cat, 'eu_sales'),
                            group_by_reg(cat, 'jp_sales')], axis=1)

    mi = pd.MultiIndex.from_frame(full_table)
    mi.names = [(r_name, p) for r_name in regions.values() for p in [cat]+pars]

    all_cat = mi.to_frame(index=False)
    

    if draw_pies:
        fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=3, figsize=(16, 8))
        regs = list(regions.values())
        for i, ax in enumerate(axes.flat):
            all_cat[[(regs[i], cat), (regs[i], 'sold (mln)')]].set_index((regs[i], cat)).plot.pie(
                y=(regs[i], 'sold (mln)'), legend=False, title=regs[i], autopct='%1.1f%%', ax=axes[i] )
        plt.subplots_adjust(left=0, bottom=0, right=1, top=1, wspace=0.1, hspace=0.5)
            
    return all_cat
